title.rendered: New Zealand vs Sri Lanka, 1st ODI 2023: Fantasy Team, Probable Playing XIs, Pitch Report & Fantasy Tips

content.rendered:
Fantasy Team for New Zealand vs Sri Lanka,1st ODI

We have opted for a fantasy cricket team on basis of probable XIs, recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable Playing XIs for New Zealand & Sri Lanka:

New Zealand: Finn Allen, Will Young, Tom Blundell, Tom Latham (c & wk), Daryl Mitchell, Glenn Phillips, Rachin Ravindra, Matt Henry, Blair Tickner, Henry Shipley, Ish Sodhi

Sri Lanka: Pathum Nissanka, Nuwanidu Fernando, Kusal Mendis (wk), Dhananjaya de Silva, Angelo Mathews, Dasun Shanaka (c), Wanindu Hasaranga, Dunith Wellalage, Chamika Karunaratne, Kasun Rajitha, Lahiru Kumara

Pitch Report for Eden Park, Auckland

Venue: Eden Park, Auckland

(Based on last three games)

1st innings average score: 243

2nd innings average score: 270

Wickets per innings: 7

Type: Balanced

Wins

Batting 1st: 33%

Batting 2nd: 67%

Also Read:

Today’s Cricket Match Schedule

Afghanistan vs Pakistan, 1st T20I Fantasy Tips

South Africa vs West Indies, 1st T20I: Fantasy Tips

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Angelo Mathews has been a delightful fantasy pick when facing New Zealand. He has scored 466 runs at 36, scalped 12 wickets, and pouched six catches.

Matt Henry loves hunting down Sri Lankan batters. In eight innings, he has scalped 21 wickets at a strike rate of 21, including two four-fors and a fifer.

Meanwhile, Ish Sodhi has scalped nine wickets at a strike rate of 27. Overall, he has featured in the Best11 in four of the last five matches.

Tom Latham averages 50 as a captain. Three of his seven centuries in ODIs have come while leading the side. At the venue, he has an average of 67 and a strike rate of 105.

Will Young smashed two centuries in the last three ODIs he played at home. During this period, he gave 28 bonus points for 21 boundaries.

Dhananjaya de Silva’s all-round ability can prove to be a boon for fantasy players: he has 194 runs, nine wickets, and four catches in the last nine ODIs.

Dasun Shanaka brings the best out of Pathum Nissanka. In 12 matches under Shanaka, Nissanka has generated a half-century or century bonus every other game, while also grabbing five catches.

Kasun Rajitha is a through-and-through strike bowler in the format, going wicketless only once in his career. In his last five outings, he took 12 wickets and hence made it to the Best11 in all these games.

Pacers scalped 70% of the wickets in the last three matches at the venue, while 12% were runouts.
